modules.description: The module provides configured logging operations, including severity-level formatting (fatal, error, warn, info, debug), output channel management, and customizable prefixes with color annotations. It works with log levels, output channels, and color specifications to tailor log visibility and structure. Use cases include applications requiring structured debugging or monitoring with visual differentiation of log entries.

Logs messages with timestamps, optional color coding for log levels, and user-defined sections. Works with strings and log levels (e.g., info, error, debug). Used to track application flow and debug issues in real-time console output.

Configures and manages logging with severity levels, output channels, and colored prefixes to enhance log readability and control. It supports operations for setting log levels, directing output, and applying visual formatting. Users can generate structured logs with distinct visual cues for different severity levels. Examples include debugging applications with color-coded warnings or redirecting logs to a file while maintaining severity-based filtering.
